The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Wednesday, June 02, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Wednesday, June 2, 2004				 																Road to avoid				 																																	Prince Anwar Shah Road. One flank dug up to lay water pipeline.				 																Soccer				 																																	The Telegraph Merchants Cup Football Tournament, organised by CC amp;FC, on the club grounds, 7.30 pm onwards.				 																Screening				 																																	Special screening of telefilm Dhando, organised by Eisenstein Cine Club and Studio Foresee, at Gorky Sadan, at 6.30 pm. Actor Gita Dey will be felicitated later.				 																Soiree				 																																	Hindustani vocal music recitals featuring Ruchira Kale (vocal), Tarak Saha (tabla) and Jyoti Goho (harmonium), at Sangeet Research Academy, at 6 pm. 				 																Talk				 																																	Dr Sarojit Dutt Memorial Lecture, presented by Public Relations Society of India (PRSI), will be delivered at Calcutta Club, at 6 pm. Speakers include Samir Goswami, national president of PRSI.				 																Launch				 																																	An exhibition of paintings will be opened with a function at Academy of Fine Arts, at 5 pm. Rituparna Sengupta, Shatabdi Roy, Abhishek Chatterjee and Tapas Pal will attend the function to celebrate the success of Bengali film Sukh Dukher Sansar.				 																Art beat				 																																	Summer Show, an all-India exhibition of paintings and sculptures, on display at CIMA Gallery, from 2 pm to 7 pm.
